title: John Fitzgerald (Rochester Broncos pitcher)
text: John J. Fitzgerald (1866 – December 20, 1892), also known as "Warren B. Fitzgerald", was an American <a href="Major%20League%20Baseball">Major League Baseball</a> player who <a href="pitcher">pitched</a> one season in the Majors with the 1890 <a href="Rochester%20Broncos">Rochester Broncos</a>. He pitched in a total of 11 <a href="games%20pitched">games</a>, <a href="games%20started">started</a> all of them, and <a href="complete%20game">completed</a> eight. He <a href="strikeout">struck out</a> 35 batters in 78 <a href="innings%20pitched">innings pitched</a>.
